                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 88.) On the 3rd of February I apprehended the prisoner going into the Cock, at Holloway, about nine o'clock in the morning—he was sober—I told him it was for a cheque belonging to Mr. Smith—he said he knew he had committed a crime and he must suffer for it—I said I must take him to the station-house—he said he expected as much—he had 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. on him—I asked what bad become of the rest of the money—he said he had lost it.</p>
